- Sat 10 Aug 2019 (Lolwa, Ituri)
[Actualite, abridged, edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/08/10/rdc-lolwa-une-nouvelle-zone-de-sante-affectee-par-ebola-en-ituri

[Byline: Christine Tshibuyi]

DRC: Lolwa, a new health zone affected by Ebola in Ituri
----------------------
A 1st confirmed case of Ebola virus disease has been detected in the locality of Lolwa, in Mambasa territory in Ituri province.

The 1st case is a 30-year-old woman "whose signs began to manifest in Some in the health zone of Mandima," the technical secretariat of the multisectoral committee of the response against the Ebola outbreak said in a bulletin on Fri [9 Aug 2019].

The woman "used self-medication from 3-4 Aug 2019 until she left Some for Lolwa and was hospitalized at the Lolwa General Hospital on 5 Aug 2019, whence the alert was issued.

"[She] has been investigated, validated and placed in isolation," the same source reported. She is still alive, and investigations to identify her contacts continue, according to the newsletter.

Lolwa is located 60 km [37.3 mi] east of the city of Mambasa, in the Babila Bakwanza chiefdom on the national road number 4, which connects the city of Bunia, capital of Ituri to Kisangani, chief town of Tshopo. This health zone is the 9th affected by Ebola in Ituri, the 27th in the 2 provinces (North Kivu and Ituri) devastated by the epidemic for a year.

Ituri alone recorded 175 deaths among the 318 confirmed and probable cases. The worst-hit health area is Katwa, with 451 deaths, Suovi de Beni, with 394 deaths, and Butembo with 312.

Another health area heavily affected by Ebola is Mabalako near Beni. It has already notified 282 deaths. All these localities are located in the northern part of North Kivu province.

