- Thu 8 Aug 2019. Disease outbreak news: Update
[WHO: Disease Outbreak News (abridged, edited)]
https://www.who.int/csr/don/08-august-2019-ebola-drc/en/

Ebola virus disease - Democratic Republic of the Congo
----------------------
The Ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreak in North Kivu and Ituri provinces in the Democratic Republic of the Congo continued this week with similar transmission intensity to recent weeks, with an average of 86 cases per week (range 80 to 91 cases per week) in the past 6 weeks (Figure 1). There are currently no confirmed cases of EVD outside of the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

In the 21 days from 17 Jul through 6 Aug 2019, 65 health areas within 16 health zones reported new cases (Table 1, Figure 2). During this period, a total of 257 confirmed cases were reported, with the majority coming from the health zones of Beni (46%, n=119) and Mandima (23%, n=58). The majority of recent cases in Mandima Health Zone were reported from the northern health areas of Some (n=39) and Mayuano (n=8). Of the 8 cases reported in Mambasa Health Zone in the past 21 days, the majority have epidemiological links to Some Health Area, with limited local transmission in Mambasa thus far.

No new confirmed cases have been reported in Goma city since our last report, with a total of 4 confirmed cases reported from Goma (n=1) and Nyiragongo (n=3) health zones to date. Of the 4 cases, 2 have died, and 2 are in an Ebola Treatment Centre (ETC). On 3 Aug 2019, all 256 contacts related to the 1st confirmed case in Goma Health Zone (reported 14 Jul 2019), finished their 21-day follow up period. A total of 232 contacts (including 114 high risk contacts) of the Nyiragongo cases remain under surveillance. Ongoing vaccination activities have reached the majority (98%) of eligible contacts, with 1314 contacts, contacts of contacts, and frontline workers vaccinated to date.

New infections continue to be reported among personnel working in community health posts and other facilities. In the last 21 days, 14 new cases were reported among health workers from Mandima (n=5), Beni (n=4), and one each in Katwa, Mambasa, Masereka, Oicha, and Vuhovi. Cumulatively, 149 (5%) healthcare workers have been infected to date.

As of 6 Aug 2019, a total of 2781 EVD cases were reported, including 2687 confirmed and 94 probable cases, of which 1866 cases died (overall case fatality ratio 67%). Of the total confirmed and probable cases, 56% (1572) were female, and 28% (791) were children aged less than 18 years.

Figure 1: Confirmed and probable Ebola virus disease cases by week of illness onset by health zone. Data as of 6 Aug 2019*
Figure 2: Confirmed and probable Ebola virus disease cases by week of illness onset by health zone. Data as of 6 Aug 2019*
Table 1: Confirmed and probable Ebola virus disease cases, and number of health areas affected, by health zone, North Kivu and Ituri provinces, Democratic Republic of the Congo, data as of 6 Aug 2019.**

