- Fri 9 Aug 2019. South Africa
[News 24, abridged, edited]
https://m.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/despite-low-risk-of-ebola-in-sa-plan-in-place-to-tackle-outbreak-20190809

Despite low risk of Ebola in SA, plan in place to tackle outbreak
------------------------
South Africa is at a low risk for an Ebola outbreak, the cabinet has said, as the deadly virus ravages the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).

Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu, International Relations and Cooperation Minister Naledi Pandor, and Health Minister Zweli Mkhize briefed the cabinet this week about the outbreak as well as the deaths caused by Ebola in the DRC and high risks posed to nearby countries.

